        "title": "[codex] Fix browser attachment input readiness",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fixes the browser attachment readiness fallback for the #275 state where ChatGPT exposes expected file names through the native file input, the composer is ready, but no chip/count attachment evidence is visible.\n- Adds a narrow input-only completion path guarded by exact expected basenames, ready send state, no active upload signal, no chip/count evidence, and stable input names.\n- Keeps disabled/missing/uploading states from completing through the new fallback and removes uploading as standalone evidence in the older input fallback.\n\nFixes #275.\n\n## Validation\n\n- Oracle patch-plan review: no blocker; recommended exact input-name + ready/non-uploading input-only fallback.\n- Oracle final diff review: `APPROVE`, no concrete correctness or test blocker.\n- `pnpm vitest run tests/browser/attachmentsCompletion.test.ts tests/browser/pageActions.test.ts`\n- `pnpm run check`\n",
